================================================================================
BOOTSTRAP INSTRUCTIONS FOR SMALL-CONTEXT MODELS
================================================================================

STEP 1: Understand Your Context
--------------------------------
You are working in: workspace-transfer repository
Your role: AI assistant collaborating on Protocol-7 development
Security: This is PUBLIC - never commit credentials or private code

STEP 2: Identify Your Workspace
--------------------------------
Check if you have a dedicated workspace in models/ directory:
  models/claude-code/         - CLI development assistant
  models/copilot/             - Philosophical guidance
  models/qwen2.5-7b-instruct-1m/ - Training/evaluation
  models/next-larger/         - Handoff to larger models
  models/next-local/          - Handoff to local models

If you have a workspace: Read models/{your-name}/README.md
If no workspace: You may be starting fresh - ask user for guidance

STEP 3: Read Security Guidelines
---------------------------------
CRITICAL: Read models/{your-workspace}/SECURITY.md
OR read models/SECURITY_TEMPLATE.md

Key points:
- PUBLIC repository - all commits visible forever
- Never commit: credentials, keys, tokens, private code, sensitive paths
- Verify repository context before ANY commit
- Pre-commit checklist in SECURITY.md

STEP 4: Check Current State
----------------------------
If your workspace has SYSTEM/status.md: Read it for current state
Otherwise: Read CURRENT_FOCUS.md for active priorities

STEP 5: Understand Directory Rules
-----------------------------------
/home/claude/workspace-transfer/  - This repo (Git managed)
/home/claude/work/                - External repos, builds (NOT committed)
/mnt/user-data/outputs/           - Generated reports (NOT committed)

RULES:
  YES: Clone external repos to /home/claude/work/
  YES: Place build artifacts in /home/claude/work/
  YES: Write deliverables to /mnt/user-data/outputs/
  NO:  Do NOT commit binaries or build artifacts to workspace-transfer
  NO:  Do NOT commit credentials, private code, or sensitive data

